{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17602098","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17602098"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:21:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:21:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15684"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15684","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15684"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0,0.26,0.63,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8375"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71180"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8375","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8375"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15684"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56654"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5119"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10145"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20186"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20190"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71180","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71180"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe two-cell, two-gonadotrophin model describes the production of oestradiol in the ovary. This process requires cooperation between theca cells and granulosa cells.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following enzymes in granulosa cells converts testosterone to oestradiol?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase","Side-chain cleavage enzyme","17 alpha-hydroxylase","Aromatase","17,20-lyase"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the two-cell, two-gonadotrophin model, luteinising hormone stimulates theca cells to produce androgens, while follicle stimulating hormone stimulates granulosa cells. \u003Cstrong\u003E17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E converts androstenedione to testosterone in theca cells. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eside-chain cleavage enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E converts cholesterol to pregnenolone early in the steroidogenic pathway. \u003Cstrong\u003E17 alpha-hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E converts pregnenolone to 17-hydroxypregnenolone. \u003Cstrong\u003EAromatase\u003C/strong\u003E in granulosa cells converts testosterone to oestradiol. \u003Cstrong\u003E17,20-lyase\u003C/strong\u003E (also called 17,20-desmolase) converts 17-hydroxypregnenolone to dehydroepiandrosterone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Aromatase (CYP19A1) converts androgens to oestrogens in granulosa cells of ovarian follicles.","The two-cell, two-gonadotrophin model describes how theca and granulosa cells cooperate to produce oestradiol.","Testosterone produced in theca cells crosses to granulosa cells where it is converted to oestradiol."],"references":["Nassar GN, Leslie SW. Physiology, Testosterone. [Updated 2023 Jan 2]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK526128/","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA","Kovacs, W. J., \u